<h2 class=3D"eplus-wrapper wp-block-heading" id=3D"0-what-is-standard-form"=
>What is Standard Form?</h2>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper">Did you know that Earth is 4,543,000,000 years =
old? We know you skipped past all those zeroes, so we will give you a simpl=
er way of saying it: Earth is 4.543 billion years old. Do you see how readi=
ng <a href=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/number-sense/numb=
er" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">numbers</a> a certain way=
 makes them easier to understand? That=E2=80=99s why all the mathematicians=
 in the world decided to agree on some rules on writing mathematical concep=
ts so that it is convenient for everyone to read, write, and work with. Thi=
s particular way is called the standard form.</p>



<figure class=3D"is-style-default wp-block-image size-full eplus-wrapper"><=
img fetchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"680" height=3D"546" =
src=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/wp-content/uploads/2022/=
05/standard_form-2-01.png" alt=3D"Standard Forms of Numbers" class=3D"wp-im=
age-3738"></figure>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper">All of the things you see in math, like numbers=
 or <a href=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/fractions/fracti=
on" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">fractions</a> or <a href=
=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/number-sense/equation" targ=
et=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">equations</a> or <a href=3D"https=
://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/number-sense/expression" target=3D"_=
blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">expressions</a>, have a standard form de=
fined for them. <strong>We can think of the standard form as the most commo=
n way of representing a mathematical element</strong>.&nbsp;</p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper">Let=E2=80=99s look at the standard form of some=
 common mathematical elements:</p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper"><strong>Whole Numbers</strong></p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper">You can <strong>define </strong>the standard fo=
rm of a <a href=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/number-sense=
/whole-numbers" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">whole number<=
/a> as follows.</p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper"><em>Any number that we can write as a <a href=
=3D"https://www.splashlearn.com/math-vocabulary/decimals/decimal" target=3D=
"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" title=3D"">decimal number</a>, between 1.0 and 10=
.0, multiplied by a power of 10, is said to be in standard form.</em></p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper"><em>For example, take the number 123,000,000; a=
n easier way of writing this number is =E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B</em></p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper"><em>1.23 =C3=97 10</em><em><sup>8</sup></em><em=
>;</em></p>



<p class=3D" eplus-wrapper">If you observe carefully, 1.23 is a decimal num=
ber between 1.0 and 10.0 and so we have the standard form of 123,000,000 as=
 1.23 =C3=97 10<sup>8</sup>.</p>



